SIMPLE: thereby
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thereby
<hw>There*by"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>By
that; by that means; in consequence of that.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Acquaint now thyself with him, and be at peace; <qex>thereby</qex>
good shall come unto thee.</q> <rj><qau>Job xxii. 21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Annexed to that.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Thereby</xex>
hangs a tale.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Thereabout; -- said of place, number, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Therefor</ent>⟦br⟧
